This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney aboard Air Force One. Carney announces that President Obama will be making a personnel announcement later in the day, nominating Shaun Donovan as the next OMB Director and Mayor Julian Castro as the new HUD Director. Carney also discusses the situation in Ukraine and the President's confidence in Russian President Putin's assurances. He talks about the qualifications of Castro and Donovan for their respective positions. Carney mentions that Rob Nabors is conducting an investigation into the Veterans Affairs issue and will be reporting to the President next week. He also briefly mentions the President's schedule for Memorial Day and meetings with lawmakers on foreign policy. The article ends with a question about the President's conversation with Mayor Emanuel and Carney's response about the President's visit to Chicago.